{{Eastern name order|Kristó Gyula}}
'''Gyula Kristó''' (11 July 1939 – 24 January 2004) was a Hungarian historian and member of the [[Hungarian Academy of Sciences]].
== Life ==
Gyula Kristó was born in Orosháza on 11 July 1939. He studied at the [[József Attila University Szeged]] between 1957 and 1962.
== Awards ==
*For the 1300-Year-Old Bulgaria (1981) *Albert Szentgyörgyi Prize (1994)
