'''Serge Afanasyan''' (13 January 1913 – 30 May 1994) was an [[Armenians|Armenian]] historian.<ref>[http://www.bibliomonde.com/auteur/serge-afanasyan-2010.html Bibliomonde profile]</ref> He was born in [[Baku]]. He wrote about the political evolution of the three [[Caucasus|Caucasian]] republics - [[Armenia]], [[Azerbaijan]] and [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]] - and in particular the story of their brief independence before the establishment of the [[Soviet]] regime (i.e. between the years 1917 and 1923). His works include ''L'Armenie, l'Azerbaidjan et la Georgie: De l'independance a l'instauration du pouvoir sovietique, 1917-1923'' and ''La Victoire de Sardarabad : Arménie, mai 1918''.<ref>[http://www.acam-france.org/bibliographie/auteur.php?cle=afanasyan-serge ACAM profile]</ref>

