'''William B. Ewald Jr.''' (December 8, 1925 – March 16, 2015) was an American speechwriter and historian for [[Dwight Eisenhower]]. He worked at the [[White House]] until 1961, when he went to be chairman of [[IBM]] until 1988.

He died of a [[respiratory failure]] at age 89.<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2015/03/18/us/william-b-ewald-jr-eisenhower-author-dies-at-89.html William B. Ewald Jr., Eisenhower Aide and Revisionist Author, Dies at 89]</ref>

